    <body>
        <p>Following are some of the key features of the <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp Mobile" /> format.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">WebHelp Features </span>This format lets you take advantage of features and benefits available with the regular <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp" /> output type.</li>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Mobile </span>This format is a good choice if your end users are on the move and need to be able to access your documentation on their mobile devices.</li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:keyword term="Language support:interface;WebHelp:language;Language support:WebHelp" /><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Multiple Languages </span>You can produce an output interface in various languages. This is possible through the use of language skins.</li>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Multiple Platforms </span>This format is a good choice if your users are working on different mobile platforms. Some of the major platforms supported are iPhone, iPad, Microsoft Mobile, LG WebOS (Palm WebOS), Blackberry, and Android.</li>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel"><MadCap:keyword term="Search;Search:optimization" />Sitemap/Search Engine Optimization (SEO) </span>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../Targets/GenerateSitemap.flsnp" />
                <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Targets/More_About_Targets/Generating_Sitemaps_for_Search_Engine_Optimization.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Generating Sitemaps for Search Engine Optimization</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</html>